data.name: _lbl_Intro1.Text
data.value:
This wizard helps you import historical data from a previous installation of SQL diagnostic manager (4.0 and later). Historical data includes all the statistics that were available on the legacy Statistics View. This data is imported into the new SQL diagnostic manager Repository.
Please note the following:
• SQL diagnostic manager 5.0 imports existing flat-file data from a 4.x installation. It does not interact with the previous releases' Metrics Repository.
• You must install SQL diagnostic manager 5.0 (the console) on the same machine as your 4.x installation in order to import.
• Servers must be registered in both 4.x and 5.0 in order to be imported.
• You must be connected to the new SQL diagnostic manager Repository as a member of the sysadmin role.

data.name: _infbx_SelectServers.Text
data.value: The Available Servers list includes all instances registered with the new SQL diagnostic manager that are SQL Server 2000 or SQL Server 2005. Select the instances you want to import, and then click the Add button.

data.name: _infbx_SelectImportDate.Text
data.value: Use the drop-down field to enter the date to which historical data should be imported for the selected SQL Server instances. All data from the selected date to the date in the Current As Of field will be imported.
